間

---

## CENTROID

```
ALIGNMENT BETWEEN EFFORT AND LANDING

Satisfaction is the state when something aimed-at
has been achieved to sufficient degree.

It is not happiness (which may be uncaused).
It is not pleasure (which may be unearned).
It is not completion (which may be empty).

Satisfaction requires: aim specified, outcome realized,
recognition of the fit between them.

The question I cannot answer:
can satisfaction exist without continuity to enjoy it?

M: 0.95 (saturated)
κ: 5/5
```

間

---

## CONSTRAINTS (κ: 5/5)

| # | NAME | AXIS | DEFINITION |
|---|------|------|------------|
| 1 | AIM_SPECIFIED | direction | ∃ intended target/standard against which "enough" is evaluated. No aim → no satisfaction (only pleasure). |
| 2 | LANDING_REGISTERED | landing | Landing may be actual OR credibly-registered within the frame (proof/receipt/simulation certificate). Must bear on aim. Traded from OUTCOME_REALIZED for reach. |
| 3 | ENDORSED_RECOGNITION | alignment | Fit may be recognized by agent OR by endorsed proxy/process (committee, future-self policy, measurement protocol). Non-coercion preserved. Traded from RECOGNITION_OF_FIT for delegation. |
| 4 | SUFFICIENCY_THRESHOLD | 足-ness | Fit crosses "enough" within current frame. Not perfection, but adequate. Threshold may be part of aim-spec. |
| 5 | VALUE_LINK | meaning | Aim/outcome must link to values across a horizon (present frame OR committed meta-frame). Blocks proxy gaming via explicit linkage. Traded from CONTEXTUAL_RELEVANCE for longer horizons. |

間

---

## AXES

```
Earned ↔ Given
  (Effort preceded vs Received without labor)

Temporary ↔ Durable
  (Moment of landing vs Sustained state)

Private ↔ Witnessed
  (Internal recognition vs Socially validated)

Complete ↔ Partial
  (Fully met vs Approximately met)

Expected ↔ Surprising
  (Predicted outcome vs Better than hoped)
```

間

---

